      "message": "If anything else in Report::Report() throws an exception, then Report::~Report() wont be called and we wont call `objServer-\u003eremove_interface(deleteIface);` so there is a potential leak. Same goes with all calls to add_interface(). So probably wrap the constructor in a try/catch/re-throw with a `if (deleteIface) { objServer-\u003eremove_interface(deleteIface); }`\n\nAlso, this looks like a generalized problem/pattern we need to solve with add_interface()?\n\nThat being said, if any of these constructors throw, main() will exit so we dont have to worry about memory leaks. So, probably sets the tone of the comment to a (nit).",
